androidx.car.navigation.utils

Class BundleMarshaller

  • java.lang.Object
    • androidx.car.navigation.utils.BundleMarshaller

  • public class BundleMarshaller
extends java.lang.Object
    Class responsible for serializing and deserializing data into a Bundle. It also provides a way to detect what items in the Bundle have been modified during marshalling.

    A single BundleMarshaller can be re-used to serialize or deserialize data multiple times. Similarity, deserialization can be done in-place, updating existing Bundlables. This reduces the number of instances being allocated.

    When serializing, use resetBundle() before marshalling and getBundle() to obtain an snap-shot of the serialized content. Or use resetDelta() and getDelta() to obtain a Bundle representing the patch between the last and the new serialized data.

    When deserializing, use setBundle(Bundle) to deserialize a Bundle containing an snap-shot, or applyDelta(Bundle) to process a patch from the last deserialized data.

    Keys used in the "get" and "put" methods must be lower camel case alphanumerical identifiers (e.g.: "distanceUnit"). Symbols like "." and "_" are reserved by the system.

    When deserializing List objects, this class assumes that they implement random access (e.g. ArrayList), or they are relatively small (see more details at #trimList(List, int))

      • applyDelta

        public void applyDelta(Bundle delta)
        Merges the provided Bundle on top of the one stored in this BundleMarshaller.
        Parameters:
        delta - a Bundle containing entries to be updated on one stored in this BundleMarshaller instance. Such Bundle can be produced by using the resetDelta() and getDelta() methods during data serialization.

      • resetDelta

        public void resetDelta()
        Resets tracking of modified entries, causing getDelta() to return an empty Bundle until the next marshalling is executed. This can be used between serializations make getDelta() return only the differences.

      • getBundlable

        @Nullable
public <T extends Bundlable> T getBundlable(@NonNull
                                                      java.lang.String key,
                                                      @Nullable
                                                      T current,
                                                      @NonNull
                                                      java.util.function.Supplier<T> factory)
        Returns the value associated with the given key, or null if no mapping of the desired type exists for the given key. If a non-null "current" instance is provided, then the deserialization would be done in place. Otherwise, a new instance will be created using the provided factory.
        Type Parameters:
        T - Bundlable type to be returned.
        Parameters:
        key - lower camel case alphanumerical identifier
        current - current value (if available) to perform in-place deserialization, or null
        factory - a Supplier capable of providing an instance of a Bundlable of type T. The suggested implementation is to pass a reference to the default constructor of that class.
        Returns:
        an instance of type T, or null
